## Summary
Set up an initial Grafana dashboard for observability, and ensure that all relevant PromQL-compatible metrics are exposed by the service endpoints. All metrics should follow Prometheus conventions (counters, gauges, histograms, etc.) and be accessible via a `/metrics` HTTP endpoint using the [prometheus_client](https://docs.rs/prometheus/) Rust crate or equivalent, if not already implemented.

## Requirements
- Ensure all listed metrics below are exposed and conform to Prometheus conventions (type, labels, naming, and help text).
- Add or update `/metrics` HTTP endpoint to expose all metrics in Prometheus format.
- Use the `prometheus` or `prometheus-client` crates for Rust.
- Set up a `grafana/provisioning/dashboards/avs-dashboard.json` file for a default dashboard, visualizing key metrics for both router and node services.
- Document dashboard import and setup in the README.
- Add example Prometheus scrape config for service discovery.
- Document how to extend metrics or dashboards.

