## Background

Social sharing of on-chain actions is growing in popularity, especially in the web3 space. Many applications now leverage shareable frames to let users celebrate and spread the word about their on-chain activities. The Morpho mini app is a good example, offering users the ability to share a custom frame to Farcaster after completing an action.

## Motivation

Currently, when a user donates (either USDC or BREAD) via the mini app, there is no way to immediately share this accomplishment or support on Farcaster or other social feeds. Introducing a shareable, exportable frame would foster a sense of community, increase transparency, and help organically promote the cause through social channels.

## Problem Statement

After a successful donation (USDC or BREAD) via the mini app, present a popup with a visually engaging frame containing:
- Confirmation of the completed donation (e.g., "You donated 10 USDC to Gaza!")
- The user’s address or handle
- Optionally, the transaction hash or a summary
- Breadfunds branding/artwork

The popup should offer:
- One-click export to Farcaster as a post
- Option to copy or download the frame as an image
- Optionally, share to other social platforms

This should be modeled after the Morpho mini app’s approach to sharing.

